      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PRETTY PRIVILEGE (3) took on a Listed race at Menangle on debut and while he only beat a couple home the stable's decision to kick him off there must be respected. Should be better for that and will find this easier. Winning hope from a good draw. Stablemate WATTS UP WOODY (7) is a colt by leading sire Captaintreacherous on debut. The driver has some work to do from this wide starting position but he looked above average in winning his latest trial in the city. BORN TO RAVISH (1) is a colt by Huntsville on debut for Dylan Xerri. Has shown some ability when a minor placegetter in two city trials and is likely to get the favours from the inside draw. Tiger Tara gelding BENJIROMAR (2) faces the starter for the first time. Should have no excuses from this advantageous draw and has been trialling well enough to be competitive.",
